     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import fitz\n",
    "import faiss\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import google.generativeai as genai\n",
    "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4558be23",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Configuring the Gemini API\n",
    "\n",
    "To generate answers from the retrieved context, Google Gemini is used as the language model.\n",
    "\n",
    "I'm using API key of Gemini"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "ef0f53eb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "genai.configure(api_key=\"GOOGLE_API_KEY")\n",
    "model = genai.GenerativeModel(\"gemini-2.5-flash\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bc85416d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Loading the PDF Document\n",
    "\n",
    "The first step of the RAG pipeline is document ingestion.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here, the selected PDF is loaded using PyMuPDF. The text from every page is extracted and combined into a single string, which will later be divided into smaller chunks for efficient retrieval."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "7472dcf4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "18000\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pdf_path = r\"C:\\Users\\laksh\\Downloads\\_OceanofPDF.com_The_Chad_Mindset_Volume_3_-_Jacked_Aecus (1).pdf\"\n",
    "doc=fitz.open(pdf_path)\n",
    "text=\"\"\n",
    "for page in doc:\n",
    "    text += page.get_text()\n",
    "print(len(text))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a40e64a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Splitting the Document into Chunks\n",
    "\n",
    "Using overlapping chunks , to preserve the context of document in large docs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "148c99cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "45\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "chunk_size=500\n",
    "overlap=100\n",
    "chunks=[]\n",
    "start=0\n",
    "while start < len(text):\n",
    "    chunks.append(text[start:start+chunk_size])\n",
    "    start += chunk_size-overlap\n",
    "print(len(chunks))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b39869b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6: Generating Text Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "The text chunks are converted into dense vector representations using the **all-MiniLM-L6-v2** Sentence Transformer model.\n",
    "\n",
    "These embeddings capture the semantic meaning of each chunk rather than just matching keywords, allowing the system to retrieve context based on meaning."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "e7a04d36",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Warning: You are sending unauthenticated requests to the HF Hub. Please set a HF_TOKEN to enable higher rate limits and faster downloads.\n",
      "Loading weights: 100%|██████████| 103/103 [00:00<00:00, 1804.67it/s]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(45, 384)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "embedder=SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
    "embeddings=embedder.encode(chunks,convert_to_numpy=True)\n",
    "print(embeddings.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c7aacea",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7: Creating the FAISS Vector Index\n",
    "\n",
    "Once the embeddings are generated, they are stored inside a FAISS index.\n",
    "\n",
    "FAISS enables extremely fast similarity search, making it possible to retrieve the most relevant chunks even from large collections of documents."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "c2f771f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "45\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "index=faiss.IndexFlatL2(embeddings.shape[1])\n",
    "index.add(embeddings.astype(\"float32\"))\n",
    "print(index.ntotal)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "201cff74",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 9: Generating Answers using Gemini\n",
    "\n",
    "The retrieved document chunks are combined with the user's question to create a prompt.\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of answering from its own knowledge, Gemini is instructed to answer only using the provided document context.\n",
    "\n",
    "This significantly reduces hallucinations and makes the responses more reliable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "286e38f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def retrieve(query,k=3):\n",
    "    q=embedder.encode([query],convert_to_numpy=True).astype(\"float32\")\n",
    "    _,idx=index.search(q,k)\n",
    "    return [chunks[i] for i in idx[0]]\n",
    "\n",
    "def ask_rag(question):\n",
    "    context=\"\\n\\n\".join(retrieve(question))\n",
    "    prompt=f'''Answer only from the context.\n",
    "\n",
    "Context:\n",
    "{context}\n",
    "\n",
    "Question:\n",
    "{question}\n",
    "'''\n",
    "    return model.generate_content(prompt).text"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7e3008ff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 10: Testing the RAG System\n",
    "\n",
    "To verify that the pipeline works correctly, a few sample questions can be asked .\n",
    "\n",
    "The system retrieves the most relevant document sections and generates answers grounded in the retrieved information.\n",
    "\n",
    "Successful responses indicate that the retrieval and generation pipeline is functioning correctly.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "eefb6ecf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The book is titled \"The Chad Mindset.\" The author believes it has the ability to change your life, and encourages readers to inculcate what they learn. It is referred to as a \"course\" and covers topics such as not feeling lonely again, emphasizing the human need for company and encouraging readers to meet and be around people.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "while True:\n",
    "    q=input(\"Question (exit to stop): \")\n",
    "    if q.lower()==\"exit\":\n",
    "        break\n",
    "    print(ask_rag(q))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5008f7d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 11: Interactive Question Answering\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, the system is converted into a simple interactive application.\n",
    "\n",
    "Users can ask any question related to the uploaded PDF, and the model will retrieve the relevant context before generating an answer.\n",
    "\n",
    ">>note:Type **exit** whenever you want to end the session."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "97ca0857",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "In this project, a complete Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline was successfully implemented.\n",
    "\n",
    "The system reads a custom PDF document, divides it into manageable chunks, converts those chunks into semantic embeddings, stores them using FAISS, retrieves the most relevant information based on user queries, and finally generates accurate answers using Google's Gemini model.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project demonstrates how retrieval improves the reliability of language models by grounding responses in real document content instead of relying only on the model's internal knowledge.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overall, this implementation provides a simple, efficient, and scalable approach for building document-based question answering systems."
   ]
  }
